x^4 - 5x^3 + 5x^2 + 5x - 6 = (x^2-2x-3)(x^2-3x+2)=(x+1)(x-3)(x-1)(x-2)
\begin{eqnarray} (x^2\!-\!2x\!-\!3)(x^2\!-\!bx\!+\!c) &=& x^4\ -\color{#0a0}{\ 5}\,\ x^3\! +\! 5x^2\! +\! 5x\! \color{#c00}{-\! 6} \\ &=& x^4\!\! -\! (\color{#0a0}{b\!+\!2})x^3+\ \cdots\ \color{#c00}{-{3}c}\end{eqnarray}
\ \Rightarrow\ 
\color{#0a0}{b=3},\,\ \color{#c00}{c=2}
\,3,-1,r,s\,
\,\color{#0a0}5 = 3\!-\!1\!+\!r\!+\!s,\,\  \color{#c00}{{-}6}= 3(-1)rs,\,
\,\color{#0a0}{r\!+\!s = 3},\,\ \color{#c00}{rs = 2}\ 
\, (x\!-\!r)(x\!-\!s) = x^2-(\color{#0a0}{r\!+\!s})x+\color{#c00}{rs} = x^2-\color{#0a0}3x+\color{#c00}2
